  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL 3 re-evaluation)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. This re-evaluation elevates the model risk level to 3 following a regulatory query regarding sensitivity of predicted hemolysis to patient-specific inlet boundary conditions. All 13 ASME V&V 40 Table 5-1 factors are addressed; 12 are formally assessed and meet or exceed their required gradation. The Use Error factor is documented as not requiring assessment because the simulation workflow is fully automated with no analyst-driven post-processing choices — however, the factor record retains factorStatus 'not-assessed' rather than 'not-applicable', creating an unrecognised gap at MRL 3.",
